	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Dec 21st 2:20 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This is an awesome weapon. My main, a 53 ShadowKnight, can hold aggro like no other using this. When I started using it, my piercing skill was only 1, at the moment, from extensive use, it is 197, and I notice a significant amout of increase in my damage over time. My old main weapon, the Argent Protector, would often hit for 30-180 every 10 seconds or so, sometimes hitting twice (taking into consideration a Flowing Black Silk Sash). This weapon hits for 13-120 every 3 seconds or so, usually hitting twice (not sure if its just luck on double attack). The damage makes this an amazing weapon when trying to hold aggro, and beautiful when soloing. I do not reccommend taunting or using excessive spells while weilding this unless you are the main tank, because other classes cannot seem to keep up. I was with a level 60 warrior, and his taunts/attacks (1HS and 1HB) versus just my attacks and a few spells (Dooming Darkness, Spear of Pain), and it was I who took the full brunt of most attacks.<br><br>My opinion, this may be the greatest &quot;non-procing&quot; SK weapon in the entire game. Specifically for loners, and masochists.<br><br>-DemitriAlexander<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
